    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<h2>tl;dr</h2>\n<p>Use <code>try-catch</code> with <code>Math.powExact</code> to avoid getting a wrong answer.</p>\n<p>No <code>for</code> loop needed.</p>\n<h2>Detect overflow</h2>\n<p>Squaring could result in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integer_overflow\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">overflow</a>, a number so large or so small that it exceeds the bounds of your numeric type (<code>int</code>, <code>long</code>).</p>\n<h3><code>…Exact</code> methods</h3>\n<p>To detect overflow, call the <code>…Exact</code> methods provided in later versions of the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Math.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>java.lang.Math</code></a> class. Trap for the expected <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/ArithmeticException.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>ArithmeticException</code></a>.</p>\n<p>Java 25 gained <code>…Exact</code> methods for <code>pow</code>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Math.html#powExact(int,int)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>powExact</code></a> (one for <code>int</code>, one for <code>long</code>)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Math.html#unsignedPowExact(int,int)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>unsignedPowExact</code></a> (one for <code>int</code>, one for <code>long</code>)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Example usage:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>try\n{\n    int squared = Math.powExact( myInt , 2 ) ;\n    int cubed = Math.powExact( myInt , 3 ) ;\n    …\n}\ncatch ( ArithmeticException  e )\n{\n    … handle overflow error \n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
